From c626665fb2aed7fb324b834305ef2584e31cdf8f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brian Goeke <bjgoeke@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Apr 2026 09:33:16 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] fix(instagram): replace dead agent-browser with puppeteer,
 add captionToRecipe, fix og:description extraction
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- server/index.js: Replace @vercel/agent-browser CLI (non-existent npm package) with
  real puppeteer-based extraction using existing getLaunchOptions() infrastructure.
  Mobile viewport, anti-detection, Instagram caption CSS selectors, carousel image extraction.
- recipeParser.js: Add captionToRecipe() — Gemini-first structuring with heuristic fallback.
  Fix detectServer() to include __SPICEHUB_SERVER__ (Vite build-time define) as first candidate.
  Update extractInstagramAgent() to use captionToRecipe instead of manual parseCaption chain.
- BrowserAssist.jsx: Add Pass 0 — for Instagram URLs, extract og:description meta tag directly
  (not full page text) and run through captionToRecipe/Gemini before any other extraction pass.
  Add 8 Instagram UI chrome patterns to PLACEHOLDER_PATTERNS (Verified, View profile, Play, etc.)
  to prevent navigation text from passing hasRealContent(). Make handleExtraction async with
  Gemini fallback after heuristic extraction fails.

Fixes: Instagram Reel imports returning "Recipe" as name with profile navigation text
as ingredients instead of actual recipe content.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
